Document: DirectionalLight2D  
Path: godot/classes/class_directionallight2d.rst  
Summary: Describes the `height` and `max_distance` properties of DirectionalLight2D, their purposes, and related methods.  

height (float): The height of the light, used with 2D normal mapping. Ranges from 0 (parallel to the plane) to 1 (perpendicular to the plane). Default: 0.0. Set via `set_height(value: float)`, get via `get_height()`.  

max_distance (float): The maximum distance from the camera center objects can be before their shadows are culled (in pixels). Decreasing this value prevents distant objects from casting shadows and improves performance. Note: `Camera2D.zoom` is not considered, so higher zoom values cause shadows to fade sooner when zooming into a point. Default: 10000.0. Set via `set_max_distance(value: float)`, get via `get_max_distance()`.